WHERE — NES · THE NES (exereunesis · the teardown)  Framework inputs: chip; bus; spec  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — A parallel-in, serial-out shift register. The CPU strobes the pad, then clocks out the eight button states one bit at a time. Dead simple, dirt cheap, and the template for game input for years.
